Class OracleTripleIterator

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator, org.apache.jena.util.iterator.ClosableIterator, org.apache.jena.util.iterator.ExtendedIterator

    public class OracleTripleIterator
extends OracleSemIterator
    An Oracle specific triple iterator that extends OracleSemIterator. Each call on next method of an instance of this class will return a Triple object.

        public OracleTripleIterator(java.sql.ResultSet rs,
                            org.apache.jena.graph.Node subject,

        Constructs a new instance based on the result set and nodes passed in.
        Parameters:
        rs - the result set of Oracle SDO_RDF_MATCH query
        subject - will be used as the subject field of the triples returned from this iterator, if not null
        predicate - will be used as the predicate field of the triples returned from this iterator, if not null
        object - will be used as the object field of the triples returned from this iterator, if not null
